                   Awesome prof. Defiantly my favorite this past semester and I had two classes with him. Speaks well & has interesting views on common subjects & the reading material in class. We were required to read the books though I didn't because he went over them in detail in class. Midterm and Final only. Attendance counts but he makes it fun to go to class.
                
                   Rosenthal is a really funny guy. No PowerPoints or outlines for the class material so it can be very hard to follow exactly what he wants you to know if you don't pay close attention to the lectures. A few pop quizzes here and there and just a midterm and final.
                
                   Be sure to go to class every day, because not only will you miss what was covered that day, but he counts your absences and WILL deduct points if you miss more than 5 in the semester. I studied for about an hour before each test and passed them easily. He is very interesting and goes by the book. Online homework three times a week, but it's easy.
                
